cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.GT, cs.SY

The paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms and their optimization for non-linear functions of long-term average rewards. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses fairness in resource allocation, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the proposed algorithm is applied to scheduling problems in cellular base-stations and queueing systems, which are examples of control systems (cs.SY).
